# Design Tokens

Source of truth: `design-tokens/` directory. W3C Design Tokens v2025.10 format.

## Rules

- All tokens use `$value` and `$type` (W3C format). Add `$description` for non-obvious tokens.
- Token names map to `--hu-*` CSS custom properties after build.
- After editing any `.tokens.json`, run `cd design-tokens && npm run build`.
- Generated outputs: CSS, Kotlin, Swift, C. Never hand-edit generated files.
- Reference `docs/standards/design/design-strategy.md` for design philosophy.

## Token Categories

| File | Key tokens added |
| --- | --- |
| `base.tokens.json` | `color.tonal.*` (M3 tonal surface primitives) |
| `semantic.tokens.json` | `surface-container`, `surface-container-high`, `surface-container-highest`, `surface-dim`, `surface-bright`, `hover-overlay` (tinted), `pressed-overlay` (tinted), `focus-overlay`, `dragged-overlay` |
| `glass.tokens.json` | `choreography.*` (enter/exit/state motion), `material.*` (Apple visionOS densities) |
| `_dynamic-color.css` | Auto-generated `--hu-dynamic-*` from OKLCH pipeline |

## Build Outputs

- `_tokens.css` — all static design tokens (CSS custom properties)
- `_dynamic-color.css` — OKLCH-generated palette (auto-built alongside tokens)
- Both are imported by `ui/src/styles/theme.css`
